brief_summary.textblock:
This withdrawn study was to assess the safety and efficacy of secukinumab compared to
      etanercept and placebo in patients who have moderate to severe, chronic, plaque-type
      psoriasis.

clinical_study.brief_title: Efficacy and Safety Study of Subcutaneous Secukinumab in Treatment of Subjects With Moderate to Severe Chronic Plaque-type Psoriasis as Compared to Etanercept and Placebo.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Chronic plaque-type psoriasis, moderate to severe

          -  Candidate for systemic therapy defined as having psoriasis not adequately controlled
             by: topical treatment, phototherapy and/or previous systemic therapy

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Forms of psoriasis other than chronic plaque-type

          -  Ongoing use of treatments not allowed for psoriasis

        Other protocol-defined inclusion/exclusion criteria may apply

intervention.description: Prefilled syringe to match experimental drug and active comparator.

clinical_study.official_title: A Randomized, Double-blind, Double-dummy, Multicenter Study of Subcutaneous Secukinumab to Demonstrate Efficacy After Twelve Weeks of Treatment, Compared to Placebo and Etanercept, and to Assess the Safety, Tolerability and Long-term Efficacy up to One Year in Subjects With Moderate to Severe Chronic Plaque-type Psoriasis.
